# Bug Analysis – Birthday Date Drift

## Problem

Birthday dates gradually shifted earlier each year.

Example:
Year 1 – Feb 22
Year 2 – Feb 21
Year 3 – Feb 20

## Cause

The application used a fixed 52-week year while real calendar years contain approximately 365 days.

365 days ≈ 52.14 weeks

This caused accumulated rounding errors.

## Attempts to Fix

1. Adding 365.25 days
2. Using UTC calculations
3. Calculating week-of-year
4. Exact day difference calculation

None fully solved the issue due to the structural mismatch between calendar time and week grid representation.

## Conclusion

The correct solution requires either:

- mapping calendar dates dynamically to week indices
or
- abandoning strict 52-week grid logic.
